.TH aws 1
.SH NAME
aws \- Run the AWS main game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aws
[\fB\-u --username\fR \fIUSERNAME\fR]
[\fB\-p --password\fR \fIPASSWORD\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aws
A fast-paced tank game. Boot up 
.B aws_server
and destroy all the enemy tanks before they get you!
.SH CONTROLS
.B Traverse (move) Hull:
.RS
.LP
\fBW\fR Move Forwards
.LP
\fBA\fR Turn Left
.LP
\fBS\fR Reverse
.LP
\fBD\fR Turn Right
.RE
.B Turn Turret:
.RS
.LP
\fB\<\- Left Arrow Key\fR Turn Turret Left
.LP
\fB\-\> Right Arrow Key\fR Turn Turret Right
.RE
.LP
.B Other Controls:
.RS
.LP
\fBSPACE\fR Fire The Gun!
.LP
.RS
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-username =\fIUSERNAME\fR
If you want to login directly without a GUI, specify your username here. 
No value here will open the GUI.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password =\fIPASSWORD\fR
If you wish, you may specify your password here. This is not required, the 
program will ask if you do not enter a value. 

